{
  "stem": "27150.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see, that means when I finished college, you see friends from [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Harrods ?] asked me to help them in the bookkeeping.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was running the bookkeeping, the illegal for-- bookkeeping for the false aliyah.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because they were, you see, at the time, after the White Paper, you see, they wouldn't let Jews into Palestine, and there was organizing you see, smuggling them through Turkey.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was helping with accounts, but not active, not actively.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, that was between '35, '38 or something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'34.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, definitely.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, that means the Poles, you see, they were tolerant, you see.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That means they keep to their own, just like we kept to our own.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Say, a Polish nobleman, a gentleman liked rather intelligent Jew's company against a peasant, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, you see, the Polish, politically, they had a national party, a moderate party and the labor party, you see, [INAUDIBLE] or something.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were hating each other, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you see, that means there was the nationals had a newspaper, you see, with a few articles against Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't like, you see, the question of they can cover economies, or something like this.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, the other Polish papers were neutral, but they were not sympathetic, but neutral, you see.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, at school that means when we went to the commercial school, we were among Poles, and they hated every other Jew, except the boys in the class, you know?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The boys in the class, they say, you Jews do this and that and that, but you're all right, you're one of us, you know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What did you think of that attitude that they had?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I thought, a matter of fact, to be friendly, frank.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
